		<p>Multidisciplinary visual artist and designer Antonyo Marest  was born on Spain's Mediterranean coast, whose warm waters and blue skies helped instil in him an optimism that has only matured with the experiences he acquired along his travels around the world. Based in Madrid since 2013, his poetic visual language, imbued with a sense of vibrancy and sensuality, draws a lot of inspiration from the bold geometry of Art Deco, the multicolour patterns of Ettore Sottsass' postmodern Memphis Group, or the dynamic forms of the Bolidista movement.</p><p>He has been exhibiting his work in solo and group shows since 2007, as well as producing works in the public space. Besides painting, sculpture, and installation, his practice further extends to graphic, industrial, interior and textile design, where he has proven able to project and adapt his creativity to different types of mediums.</p><p><a href="https://antonyomarest.es/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>www.antonyomarest.es</strong></a></p>		
